msgid ""
"\\>\\c[6]\n"
"              Valnar und Aysha Darnus."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[6]\n"
"\\>             \\_Valnar and Aysha Darnus"

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Aysha ist die langjährige Freundin von Valnar.\n"
"Sie lernte ihn während eines Festes in \\c[4]Limm\n"
"\\>\\c[2]kennen."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Aysha has been Valnar's girlfriend for many years\n"
"now. She met him at a festival in \\c[4]Klennar\\c[2]."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Seit vier Jahren leben sie nun gemeinsam in dieser\n"
"Stadt. Sie ist eine hübsche junge Dame,\n"
"allerdings ist sie ziemlich\n"
"abweisend anderen gegenüber."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]They have been living in this town for 4 years\n"
"now. She is an attractive young woman. But she is\n"
"also fairly dismissive towards others."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]In letzter Zeit schien sie etwas zu bedrücken.\n"
"Doch Valnar konnte nie herausfinden, was\n"
"sie beschäftigt."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Recently, something seemed to have been bothering\n"
"her, but Valnar could never find out what it was."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Valnar ist ein junger Kämpfer aus \\c[4]Limm\\c[2],\n"
"einer Stadt nördlich von \\c[4]Klennar.\\c[2] Als\n"
"seine Eltern verstarben, war Valnar bereits\n"
"alt genug, um sich selbst zu versorgen."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Valnar is a young warrior from \\c[4]Limm\\c[2], a town north\n"
"of \\c[4]Klennar\\c[2]. When his parents died, he was already\n"
"old enough to take care of himself."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Er kämpft mit großer Leidenschaft, doch seit\n"
"er diesen Traum das erste Mal vor vier Wochen\n"
"hatte, wurde er immer nervöser und\n"
"zerbrechlicher."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]He fights with great passion, but ever since he\n"
"started having those dreams four weeks ago, he has\n"
"become more nervous and frail."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Er leidet stark unter diesem immer wieder-\n"
"kehrenden Alptraum."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]He suffers greatly because of these returning\n"
"nightmares."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Doch erhält er Mut und Geborgenheit durch\n"
"seine Freundin Aysha, die ihn immer wieder\n"
"versucht aufzumuntern."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Though he does find courage and comfort through\n"
"his girlfrind Aysha, who always tries to cheer him\n"
"up."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[1]\n"
"                 Alaine Frynia"
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[1]\n"
"\\>                  \\_Alaine Frynia"

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Alaine ist eine sehr junge und\n"
"hübsche Dame.\\.\\. Und doch meinte\n"
"es das Schicksal schlecht mit ihr."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Alaine is a very young and pretty woman.\n"
"\\.\\.Yet fate was not kind to her."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Man fand sie eines Tages \n"
"bewusstlos in einer Stadt. Niemand\n"
"wusste wer sie war, oder woher sie kam. "
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]One day, she was found unconscious in some town.\n"
"Nobody knew who she was or where she was from."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Keiner kannte ihren Namen.\n"
"Die Menschen sahen nur ihren hilflosen\n"
"Körper am Stadtrand. Ein Arzt holte\n"
"sie in sein Haus, und fing an sie zu"
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Nobody knew her name. The people just saw her\n"
"helpless body on the side road. A doctor took her\n"
"to his house and started taking care of her."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]pflegen. Doch es half nichts.\n"
"\\.\\.Alaine blieb weiterhin ohne\n"
"Bewußtsein."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]But it didn't help.\n"
"\\.\\.Alaine remained unconscious."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Die Leute begannen von einer\n"
"Krankheit zu reden, die bald alle\n"
"Bewohner anstecken würde."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]The people started speculating about a disease\n"
"that could potentially infect all of them soon as\n"
"well."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Kurze Zeit später erwachte\n"
"sie urplötzlich aus ihrem Koma.\n"
"\\.\\.Doch sie konnte sich an nichts\n"
"erinnern. Sie war nicht einmal mehr"
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Suddenly she woke up shortly afterwards.\n"
"\\.\\.But she couldn't remember anything. She wasn't\n"
"even able to think clearly."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]in der Lage, klar zu denken.\n"
"\\.\\.Das Sprechen blieb ihr völlig \n"
"versagt.\\.\\. Die Bürger der Stadt waren \n"
"ebenso ratlos wie der Arzt."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]She was completely incapable of speaking.\n"
"\\.\\.The citizens of the town were as clueless as the\n"
"doctor."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Ihre Unfähigkeit klar zu denken\n"
"und zu reden bestätigte die Bürger\n"
"nur in ihrem Glauben, dass es sich\n"
"um eine Krankheit handeln müsste."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Her inability to talk and to think straight\n"
"strengthened the beliefs of the people that it\n"
"must have been some kind of disease."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]So kam es, dass Alaine aus dieser Stadt \n"
"verbannt wurde.\n"
"\\.\\.Sie wurde nach \\c[4]Shannar\\c[2] gebracht,\n"
"wo sie nun im Irrenhaus ihr Dasein fristet."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]And so it came that Alaine was banished\n"
"from the town. \\.\\.\n"
"She was brought to \\c[4]Shannar\\c[2], where she\n"
"was now living in an asylum,"

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Zusammen mit anderen, angeblich \n"
"kranken, Menschen, deren\n"
"Symptome ebenso unerklärlich sind."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]together with other seemingly sick people whose\n"
"symptons were as inexplicable as hers. "

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Einzig und allein eine Kette\n"
"mit ihrem Namen hält sie davon\n"
"ab, zu glauben, dass sie nicht mehr\n"
"existiert oder nie existiert hat !"
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Only a necklace with her\n"
"name on it stops her from believing she doesn't\n"
"exist anymore, or even that she has never existed\n"
"to begin with!"

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[1]\n"
"                 Asgar Serran"
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[1]\n"
"\\>                   Asgar Serran"

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Asgar ist ein Vampir.\n"
"\\.\\.\\.Geboren vor 400 Jahren, in einer\n"
"Zeit, als Vampire das Land überfluteten."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Asgar is a vampire.\n"
"\\.\\.\\.Born 400 years ago during a time when the lands\n"
"were filled with vampires."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Seine Eltern wurden von Vampiren\n"
"getötet, und er selber wurde von einem\n"
"gebissen, sodass er nun als Untoter\n"
"verflucht durch das Land streift."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]His parents were killed by vampires, and he\n"
"himself was bitten by one. Now he is wandering the\n"
"lands as a cursed undead being."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]An seinem ersten Tag als Vampir\n"
"schwor er, seinen Schöpfer zu vernichten.\n"
"Doch er musste diesen Kampf verschieben,\n"
"da in diesem Jahrzehnt der große"
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]He swore to himself on his first day as a vampire\n"
"that he would kill his sire. But he had no choice\n"
"but to postpone that battle, because that year\n"
"was when the great crusade against the vampires"

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Kreuzzug gegen die Vampire\n"
"begann. Dieser Kreuzzug stand unter\n"
"der Kontrolle des Priesters \\c[1]Vincent Weynard\\c[2]."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]began. That crusade was led by a priest named\n"
"\\>\\c[1]Vincent Weynard\\c[2]."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Fast alle Vampire wurden vernichtet,\n"
"und die wenigen, die diesen Kreuzzug\n"
"überlebten, verbrachten ihr weiteres\n"
"Leben im Geheimen, vor Angst eines"
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Nearly all vampires had been wiped out, and the\n"
"few that survived spent their remaining days\n"
"hidden in fear of another massacre."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]neuen Massakers. Doch die Zeit\n"
"verann, und \\c[1]Vincent Weynard\\c[2]\n"
"wurde älter und starb. Asgar sah jetzt \n"
"seine Zeit gekommen und suchte"
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]But time passed, and \\c[1]Vincent Weynard\\c[2] \n"
"grew older and passed away. Asgar saw that his \n"
"time had come\n"
" to search for his creator"

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]seinen Schöpfer um ihn zu\n"
"vernichten und damit seine Seele\n"
"zu rächen. Doch bisher blieb seine\n"
"Suche erfolglos."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]and kill him in Revenge for his soul.\n"
"But so far, his hunt had been unsuccessful."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Er unterbrach sie um\n"
"eine feste Unterkunft für sich zu suchen.\n"
"Er kam zu einem bewohnten Schloß\n"
"auf der Spitze eines Berges."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]He interrupted his search to look\n"
"for a permanent place to live. He arrived at an\n"
"occupied castle on top of a mountain."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Nachdem er die bisherigen Bewohner\n"
"getötet und versklavt hat, erkundete\n"
"er die Umgebung dieses Schlosses."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]After he enslaved and killed the previous\n"
"inhabitants, he explored the surrounding areas of\n"
"the castle."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Eines Tages kam er nach \\c[4]Shannar\\c[2],\n"
"wo er Alaine traf. Sie ist unheilbar krank, kann\n"
"nicht sprechen und ist häufig von \n"
"unkontrollierbaren Krämpfen geplagt."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]One day he arrived in \\c[4]Shannar\\c[2], where he met\n"
"Alaine. She was incurably sick, couldn't speak,\n"
"and was occasionally plagued by uncontrollable\n"
"cramps."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Überwältigt von ihrer Schönheit,\n"
"wuchs der letzte Funke Menschlichkeit in\n"
"ihm, und er verliebte sich ungewöhnlicherweise\n"
"in sie."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Overwhelmed by her beauty, the last bit of\n"
"humanity grew in him, and he fell unexpectedly in\n"
"love with her."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Seitdem besucht er sie regelmäßig \n"
"in ihrem Gefängnis und sucht ein Heilmittel\n"
"für ihre Krankheit."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]Ever since then, he had been visiting her on a\n"
"regular basis, and he was trying to find a cure\n"
"for her sickness."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Asgar bekam bei seiner Geburt als\n"
"Vampir die dunkle Gabe, sich in einen\n"
"Schatten zu verwandeln, was ihn\n"
"für alle Lebewesen unsichtbar macht."
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]At his birth as a vampire, he obtained a dark gift\n"
"that allowed him to turn himself into a shadow,\n"
"which made him invisible for any living being."

msgid ""
"\\>\\c[2]Auch ist er als Schatten in der Lage,\n"
"durch Gegenstände hindurch zu gehen,\n"
"wodurch er überall hingelangt. "
msgstr ""
"\\>\\c[2]It also allowed him to walk through solid objects,\n"
"which made it possible for him to reach all kinds\n"
"of different places."
